    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to small objects of prehistoric art, especially of the Upper Palaeolithic, that could be carried from place to place, as opposed to cave art. Examples include small figures, carved tools, or pieces of jewelry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
